check_mk Plugin to check php opcacher modul XCache.

The agent plugin will check the status of xcache.
Please install and configure the xcache php module 
and put the xcache_status.php file in the webserver root directory.

The check was tested on the following Linux versions: Debian Wheezy (xcache 2.0.0)

Any feedback welcome, PM to karsten.schoeke[at]geobasis-bb[dot]de. 
I'm also reading the german check_mk ML: checkmk-de@lists.mathias-kettner.de

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS

On your check_mk clients:
Put xcache_status.php into the webserver root directory
Install the check_mk agent plugin under
/usr/lib/check_mk/plugins/
Create a file named /etc/check_mk/xcache_status.conf,
for customize your webserver settings.

On your check server:
Install the xcache-x.x.mk package.
